{"author":{"id":"1abd2d772d27f1502e8e46f73e56c7abc71f56a01ea56f59152f24b2962d92fb"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1627483755,"nonce":"WYJNGSW8UR1qgZBpi9KR+NwHy9k=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s4083_n","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3848#issuecomment-888373223"},"message":"Hi @bernt-matthias \n\nThanks for the message and details.  It was interesting that the image said that the collection should be sorted after it is unzipped because I hadn't done this. I sorted the unzipped collection but I got the same result unfortunately. \n\nI also ran filterAndTrim before the forwards and reverse reads were unzipped. However, the filterAndTrim has the option to take paired collection data and the summary stats stats are the same for the R package so I think this is okay.\n\nAs far as I am aware, I have applied learnErrors and dada on the forward and reverse reads independently. See workflow here https://usegalaxy.eu/u/ollie_white/w/dada2-tutorial-pipeline for more details\n\nI noticed the parameter for the 'Magnitude of number of bases to use for learning'. I assumed this is the same as nbases in for the learnErrors command in R, which has a default value of 1e8. I left this as 8 to match the default for the R package. Note that I tried to increase this value in Galaxy but I got the same result again.\n\nWould be great to know what you think? I would like to use dada2 for a training course and I just want to make sure I can replicate the tutorial.\n\nCheers\nOllie","files":null},{"type":6,"timestamp":1627483786,"nonce":"Tu7gHs51M4r2qHeWOmEd2mo8jMw=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6NDgyNDY0MDk3"},"target":"a76781e52334778e905b1677297b98753895c5d99e0da4aecad8aaa22a74ea8b","message":"Hi @bernt-matthias \n\nThanks for the message and details.  It was interesting that the image said that the collection should be sorted after it is unzipped because I hadn't done this. I sorted the unzipped collection but I got the same result unfortunately. \n\nI also ran filterAndTrim before the forwards and reverse reads were unzipped. However, the filterAndTrim has the option to take paired collection data and the summary stats are the same for the R package so I think this is okay.\n\nAs far as I am aware, I have applied learnErrors and dada on the forward and reverse reads independently. See workflow here https://usegalaxy.eu/u/ollie_white/w/dada2-tutorial-pipeline for more details\n\nI noticed the parameter for the 'Magnitude of number of bases to use for learning'. I assumed this is the same as nbases in for the learnErrors command in R, which has a default value of 1e8. I left this as 8 to match the default for the R package. Note that I tried to increase this value in Galaxy but I got the same result again.\n\nWould be great to know what you think? I would like to use dada2 for a training course and I just want to make sure I can replicate the tutorial.\n\nCheers\nOllie","files":null}]}